  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators will continue their work with implanted stimulators to improve bladder and
      bowel function. Electrical stimulation produces simultaneous contraction of sphincters with
      the target organs, making emptying difficult. By optimizing electrode placement, employing a
      new electrode design and waveform choice, it is hoped to improve the 50% of subjects able to
      defecate with existing approaches. This is part of a multi-center study with multiple support
      sources, including Rehab R&amp;D, PVA and a commercial stimulator company.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
